{
  "hash": "6abb6934ae05d4d1e9b12efa0e8b6b7113fb0dc5",
  "title": "B2B inspector uploads a valid DOCX attachment",
  "spec": "document/document-upload-valid-inspector.spec.ts:54 › Valid inspector attachment upload › CHED-PP › B2B inspector uploads a valid DOCX attachment",
  "relevance": "post-submission",
  "outcome": "A trader creates and submits a complete CHED-PP pre-notification end-to-end (commodity codes 06011010 and 06042090, packaging, transport to BCP, an accompanying document with a DOCX attachment, consignor and consignee addresses, declaration), captures the issued reference CHEDPP.GB.2026.1525839, then a second browser context signs in as a B2B border inspector on the internal host, searches the BIP notification list for that CHED number, opens its Attachments tab, and uploads a further DOCX (INS-UPLOAD) which then appears as a viewable link in the inspector documents table.",
  "notes": [
    "Two distinct hosts: the trader journey runs on importnotification-static-snd.azure.defra.cloud (/notification/...), the inspector journey on importnotification-int-static-snd.azure.defra.cloud (/decision/...).",
    "File upload is a THIRD app mounted at /upload/vnet/protected/upload/<ref>/<idx>/<context>/attach, where <context> is 'notification' for the trader and 'decision' for the inspector. Both journeys leave the owning app to upload, then return.",
    "The draft is identified as DRAFT.GB.2026.1525839 throughout, and the SAME numeric suffix is retained on submission as CHEDPP.GB.2026.1525839 — the CHED type prefix replaces DRAFT rather than a new id being minted.",
    "'Commodity code search' is a govuk-tabs TAB within consignment/page-3 (?tab=commodity-code-search), not a separate page — the prior extraction's page split at actions 17-20/26-29 is a tab switch.",
    "The commodity leg is entered twice: once inline in the linear flow (actions 17-21) and once by returning from the task-list hub via the 'Commodity' link (actions 24-30) to add a second commodity.",
    "Actions 95 and 96 both click 'Search' — the first click appears not to have produced results, so the test clicks again before waiting for the result link."
  ],
